{{Politics of Denmark}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in [[Denmark]] on 23 May 1939.<ref name=DN>[[Dieter Nohlen]] & Philip Stöver (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p524 {{ISBN|978-3-8329-5609-7}}</ref> Voters were asked whether they approved of a new [[Constitution of Denmark|constitution]]. Although it was approved by 91.9% of those who voted, a turnout of only 48.9% meant that the percentage of eligible voters approving it was only 44.46%, below the 45% required by the existing constitution of 1915.<ref>Nohlen & Stöver, p505</ref>
==Proposed changes from the existing constitution== The two primary changes in the proposed constitution from 1939 was lowering the electoral age from 25 to 23 years, and replacing the [[Landsting (Denmark)|Landsting]] with a new [[Chambers of parliament|chamber]] of parliament, the Rigsting.<ref name=wendt>Wendt, Frantz W. (1951). "Rigsdagen 1915-40", in Bomholt, J., Fabricius, K., Hjelholt, H., Mackeprang, M. & Møller, A. (eds.): ''Den Danske Rigsdag 1849-1949 bind II - Rigsdagens histore 1866-1949'' {{da icon}}. Copenhagen: J. H. Schultz Forlag, pp. 554-556.</ref> Additionally, the united parliament ({{lang-da|den forenede [[rigsdag]]}}) consisting of the members of the two other chambers was to become a third chamber of parliament.<ref name=skou>Skou, Kaare R. (2005). ''Dansk politik A-Å'' {{da icon}}. Aschehoug, pp. 579-580. {{ISBN|87-11-11652-8}}.</ref> The united parliament would handle the more important types of bills, including the Budget and proposed changes to the constitution.<ref name=wendt /> Other bills could be proposed in either the Folketing or the Rigsting, and in order to pass they would have to go through three readings in the chamber, in which they were proposed, and two readings in the other.<ref name=skou /> This would have been a simplification of the existing process where all bills had to go through three readings in each of the two chambers.
==Results== {| class=wikitable style=text-align:right !Choice !Votes !% |- |align=left|For||966,277||91.9 |- |align=left|Against||85,717||8.1 |- |align=left|Invalid/blank votes||11,770||– |- |align=left|'''Total'''||'''1,063,764'''||'''100''' |- |align=left|Registered voters/turnout||2,173,420||48.9 |- |align=left colspan=3|Source: Nohlen & Stöver |}
==Aftermath== The Danish constitution was finally altered to its present form following a [[Danish constitutional and electoral age referendum, 1953|1953 referendum]].
