{{Infobox U.S. legislation | shorttitle = Depository Library Act of 1962 | othershorttitles = | longtitle = An Act to revise the laws relating to depository libraries. | colloquialacronym = DLA | nickname = | enacted by = 87th | effective date = August 9, 1962 | public law url = http://www.gpo.gov/fdsys/pkg/STATUTE-76/pdf/STATUTE-76-Pg352.pdf | cite public law = 87-579 | cite statutes at large = {{usstat|76|352}} | acts amended = | acts repealed = | title amended = [[Title 44 of the United States Code|44 U.S.C.: Public Printing and Documents]] | sections created = {{Usc-title-chap|44|19}} § 1901 et seq. | sections amended = | leghisturl = | introducedin = House | introducedbill = {{USBill|87|H.R.|8141}} | introducedby = [[Wayne Hays]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]]–[[Ohio|OH]]) | introduceddate = July 17, 1962 | committees = [[United States House Committee on House Administration|House Administration]], [[United States Senate Committee on Rules and Administration|Senate Rules and Administration]] | passedbody1 = House | passeddate1 = August 22, 1961 | passedvote1 = passed | passedbody2 = Senate | passedas2 = <!-- used if the second body changes the name of the legislation --> | passeddate2 = June 15, 1962 | passedvote2 = passed | conferencedate = | passedbody3 = | passeddate3 = | passedvote3 = | agreedbody3 = House | agreeddate3 = July 18, 1962 | agreedvote3 = agreed | agreedbody4 = Senate | agreeddate4 = July 25, 1962 | agreedvote4 = agreed | passedbody4 = | passeddate4 = | passedvote4 = | signedpresident = [[John F. Kennedy]] | signeddate = August 9, 1962 | unsignedpresident = <!-- used when passed without presidential signing --> | unsigneddate = <!-- used when passed without presidential signing --> | vetoedpresident = <!-- used when passed by overriding presidential veto --> | vetoeddate = <!-- used when passed by overriding presidential veto --> | overriddenbody1 = <!-- used when passed by overriding presidential veto --> | overriddendate1 = <!-- used when passed by overriding presidential veto --> | overriddenvote1 = <!-- used when passed by overriding presidential veto --> | overriddenbody2 = <!-- used when passed by overriding presidential veto --> | overriddendate2 = <!-- used when passed by overriding presidential veto --> | overriddenvote2 = <!-- used when passed by overriding presidential veto --> | amendments = | SCOTUS cases = }} '''Depository Library Act of 1962''' is a [[Law of the United States|federal statute]] revising the [[Legal deposit|depository library]] laws passed in the [[United States]] from 1895 to 1939. The [[Act of Congress]] mandated the availability of U.S. government publications through the [[United States Government Publishing Office|Superintendent of Documents]] for public information. The statute established requirements for two depository libraries as allocated by [[United States Congress|U.S. Congressional representatives]] per their respective [[United States congressional apportionment|congressional districts]]. The U.S. federal law provided provisions appointing [[Land-grant university|land-grant colleges]] and the [[United States service academies]] as depository libraries for U.S. government publications. The 87th U.S. Congressional [[legislation]] authorized regional depository libraries allocating two depository libraries per [[U.S. state]] as defined by a [[United States Senate|United States Senator]]. The Act [[repeal]]ed Public Law 76-281 designating the [[United States Coast Guard Academy]] library as a depository of U.S. government publications while redelegating the [[New London, Connecticut]] office of the Superintendent of Documents.
