[[File:Sofia - Ministry of Justice.JPG|thumb|300x300px|The building of the Ministry of Justice on 1 Slavyanska Street in [[Sofia|София]]]] Established by Decree No 1 of July 5, 1879, the '''Ministry of Justice of Bulgaria''' is the link between the [[Executive (government)|executive]] and [[judicial]] [[Separation of powers|branches of power]]. It directs the writing of new laws related to the judiciary and offers feedback on laws prepared by other government organizations.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.justice.government.bg/6/|title = Министър: Правомощия и отговорности|trans-title = Minister: Powers and Obligations |publisher = Ministry of Justice official website|access-date = 3 August 2015}}</ref>
